Tell me your latest win that you’re really proud of!! I had a chat with @craftychica on Friday and she reminded me how important it is to acknowledge your wins. She said, “Write it on the mirror in red lipstick!”. This is my equivalent, lol. I work alone and am often jumping from one deadline to the other and I am rarely (read: never) taking the time to sit back and admire all that I’ve done. So, this is my promising myself to spend some more time doing that. Here are some recent wins I would like to acknowledge:
-I sold out of WOY mug preorders with no advertising other than three Instagram posts
-The bisque line that I designed for @bisqueimports sells really well- to the point some designs are temporarily sold out 🤯
-I’m headed out in less than 2 weeks for my first teaching gig of the year. I am so honored companies I admire want to host me at their events to teach classes.
-I was able to take almost a month off from work because of a successful Yalliday season. THANK YOU!!

You asked so here it is- my homemade popcorn seasoning. This is absolutely adapted from @sohlae’s popcorn seasoning (if not it exactly, I can’t remember!) and it’s so good. I do not measure so don’t ask me for the exact amounts. I just pour it into my mortar and pestle and grind to a fine powder, then store in an air tight container. I like to make about a 1/2 cup at a time so I can keep it on hand for when the craving strikes. I prefer stovetop popcorn but hate cleaning the pot so shoutout to the silicone microwave popcorn poppers. Y’all are the realest.

Tomorrow is the day! Come prepared and make an account (“purchase” the rainbow mug color chart to set up an account for free. If you’ve purchased from me before you likely already have an account) and your chances of getting a mug are high. I get comments frequently about how people have tried multiple times and they can’t get anything and I totally hear you and wish I could offer unlimited preorders of items but the time it takes to work through 100+ orders stresses me out. Plus, the smaller the preorder, the faster I can work through it. Also!! I have repeat customers every round of ordering or some customers that are able to place two orders in one preorder. You just gotta come prepared and not dilly dally. If the orders open at 3pm est (they do) and you show up at 3:04 to order, DO NOT be upset with me that the mugs are gone. If you’re late for the bus it’ll leave without you! I’m opening orders to Canada for this round but shipping will be slightly more expensive because it is more expensive for me. Let me know if you have any questions! Love y’all!

Sometimes I get embarrassed when I set my camera up to film a workout. I always try to do it quickly and as inconspicuous as possible because I don’t want people to see me and think, I don’t know, that i shouldn’t be recording because I’m not great at some moves or my progression isn’t impressive. I always joke that I perform better for the camera whenever people notice. I worry people will think I’m being self indulgent or Too On the Internet when I record. But I’m so so happy to have a video diary of this journey (two years next month!) because I don’t always feel like I’m growing or changing until I see old videos. This particular clip is my first time progressing to the trap bars and I was (am!) so proud. I ran it by coaches first and they agreed my back and I were ready for it and checked my form along the way. I’ve revisited this clip many times because I can’t believe I can do something like this. I am grateful for my gym, my coaches, my body, my mind, and duh, my phone. ♥️
